reviewText: decent storydreadful copy. I expected better from Warner Bros.colour keeps changing which is very distracting.

The picture quality on this Warner Archive movie is terrible. The image is soft and the color shifts all over the place. Lots of red in the dissolves. Goes from dark to light whenever it feels like it. This needs restoration in the worst way. I've seen bootlegs that look better than this. The movie is all right but come on fellas, if you're gonna dish this sub-quality out then do it at the price it's worth--$3.00.
Allan Ladd, what can I say.  Good movie.  There are a few more movies to add to his collection, such as Red Mountain.  I enjoy watching this movie.

Good story and acted by the leading actors of the time.  Alan Ladd and Gilbert Roland were very good and the film was
directed beautifully in a great location.
A great movie with great actors.
